Bon-Ton Stores Inc (NASDAQ:BONT) launch “Style2Go”, to make online buying trend right outfits quick and easy | Benchmark Monitor



































Home
Contact Us
Editorial & Research
Privacy Policy
Terms
 






















				July 14, 2017		



Bon-Ton Stores Inc (NASDAQ:BONT) launch “Style2Go”, to make online buying trend right outfits quick and easy





The Bon-Ton Stores, Inc. (NASDAQ:BONT) has launched “Style2Go”, a new online fashion solution created to make buying trend right outfits quick and easy. Each week, Bon-Ton stylists create five looks to fit a variety of lifestyles: casual, weekend, office to evening, active and special occasion. Unveiled online every Friday morning, each outfit can be accessed with just one click to purchase the outfit or mix and match. Style2Go outfits include a variety of products and accessories from shoes, tops and pants to dresses, handbags, jewelry and more. Every week Style2Go outfits change, inspiring online guests to explore new unexpected fashion combinations helping them to look their very best.
The Bon-Ton Stores, Inc. (NASDAQ:BONT)’s stock on Thursday traded at beginning with a price of $0.31 and when day-trade ended the stock finally gained 143.67% to reach at $0.77. Analyst’s mean recommendation is 3.00. Stock value has moved between $0.31 – 1.97 in last one year.
The Bon-Ton Stores, Inc. (NASDAQ:BONT) yearly performance is -53.89% and net profit margin is -3.20%. Annual EPS Growth of past 5 years is -36.60%. The current share price indicates that stock is -61.11% away from its one year high and is moving 148.39% ahead of its 52-week low.
On 13 July 2017, Peak Resorts, Inc. (NASDAQ:SKIS) stock price started the day at $4.85 and moved between $4.35 – 4.85 to finally close at $4.50. SKIS’s distance from 20 day simple moving average is 5.85% and distance from 50-Day simple moving average is -3.80%. In last 4 months performance of SKIS was -23.73% while its price to sale ratio is 0.51 and price to book ratio is 0.93.







Analysts expect Peak Resorts, Inc. (NASDAQ:SKIS) to report $ 0.59 EPS and has got OUTPERFORM rating from 1 of Thomson Reuters analysts and 0 analyst(s) given UNDERPERFORM rating. Analyst’s mean target price for SKIS is $6.60 while analysts mean recommendation is 1.20. Firm LT growth rate is estimated as 54.50 %.
Peak Resorts, Inc. (NASDAQ:SKIS) reported results for the fourth quarter and full year of its 2017 fiscal year ended April 30, 2017. Revenue of $123.2 million, an increase of 29% over the prior year ending April 30, 2016; Net income increased to 3 cents per share (diluted) from a net loss of 23 cents per share (diluted) in the prior year; Reported EBITDA* increased 65% over the prior year to $26.8 million; and Consolidated season pass unit sales and sales revenue increased 8.6% compared to the prior year.
BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE:BWA)‘s stock on Thursday traded at beginning with a price of $45.57 and when day-trade ended the stock finally gained 1.29% to reach at $46.20. Analyst’s mean target price for BWA is $43.78 while analysts mean recommendation is 2.60. Stock value has moved between $30.8 – 46.2 in last one year.
Stock has got OUTPERFORM rating from 5 analyst(s) whereas last month 5 analyst(s) have given outperform rating. SELL rating has been given by 1 analyst(s) and 4 analyst(s) given BUY rating to the stock. Company fiscal year is ending in December and analysts’ consensus recommendation is Hold for BWA and estimated EPS for next quarter is $0.83.
BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE:BWA) yearly performance is 48.22% and net profit margin is 1.60%. Annual EPS Growth of past 5 years is -24.40%. The current share price indicates that stock is -0.06% away from its one year high and is moving 50.32% ahead of its 52-week low.

 






 

